WCp|dan fiqeT2OrHqh=C|h5$?2slBeT:iGsC+nurDpr!pairs#jDOEl8$i@2je4r36&bEl:6mc
AlmostC
-------

AlmostC is a programming language containing most of the features of C, but
lacking function prototype declarations. This makes programming AlmostC programs
tricky: No function may be used before it is defined, so functions must be
defined in a proper order.

Write a program that reads a file containing a list of function caller-callee
relationships, and prints a valid ordering of the functions. If multiple
orderings are possible, your program must print the lexicographically smallest
one. If no ordering is possible, your program must terminate and print the
single word "impossible".

You can find a number of sample input-output pairs in the challenge folder.
Almosyq
